00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:20.180
So, I was wondering if you would show me what you show other people.

00:18:20.180 --> 00:18:24.180
Of course, I'm really sorry to hear that about your mom.

00:18:24.180 --> 00:18:33.690
Did you know that the Bible actually gives us the hope for a resurrection?

00:18:33.690 --> 00:18:37.690
Next, we have Brother Ben Matthews with us.

00:18:37.690 --> 00:18:45.690
Brother Matthews, you've been able to raise a family, serve as an elder and pioneer for many years.

00:18:45.690 --> 00:18:48.690
What a good example of faith and courage.

00:18:48.690 --> 00:18:51.690
Thank you, Brother Nicoletti.

00:18:51.690 --> 00:18:57.690
But truthfully, courage isn't something that comes easy to me.

00:18:57.690 --> 00:18:59.690
I have to keep working on it.

00:18:59.690 --> 00:19:00.690
Why is that?

00:19:00.690 --> 00:19:06.690
Well, I remember years ago when my wife Abby became very ill.

00:19:06.690 --> 00:19:13.690
She was in the hospital for months while I cared for our newborn son and young daughter.

00:19:13.690 --> 00:19:15.690
I didn't know if she would ever recover.

00:19:15.690 --> 00:19:21.690
I prayed and prayed and it appeared as if nothing changed.

00:19:21.690 --> 00:19:27.690
I could feel my faith beginning to crack and give way to doubt.

00:19:27.690 --> 00:19:32.690
I even started doubting Jehovah's promises for the future.

00:19:32.690 --> 00:19:34.690
So, what changed that?

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:37.690
A friend stepped in at the right time.

00:19:37.690 --> 00:19:43.690
He encouraged me when I was home alone to read David's words at Psalm 27.

00:19:43.690 --> 00:19:46.690
At first, I didn't want to.

00:19:46.690 --> 00:19:48.690
But eventually, I did.

00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:53.690
And something about those words touched my heart.

00:19:53.690 --> 00:19:59.690
You see, like a plant deprived of water, I was starving my faith.

00:19:59.690 --> 00:20:05.690
So, I kept reading and meditating on those words in Psalm 27.

00:20:05.690 --> 00:20:09.690
And eventually, my doubts began to melt away.

00:20:09.690 --> 00:20:12.690
But as you mentioned, Brother Matthews, that was decades ago.

00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:16.690
You said courage is something that you're continuing to work on.

00:20:16.690 --> 00:20:21.690
Well, for much of my life, I've had to help other people be courageous.

00:20:21.690 --> 00:20:31.450
But recently, I found out that soon, I will go blind.

00:20:31.450 --> 00:20:38.450
Between this and not being able to do as much in the congregation as I used to,

00:20:38.450 --> 00:20:42.450
well, I could feel those doubts creeping up again.

00:20:42.450 --> 00:20:48.450
I think it's easier to help others be courageous.

00:20:48.450 --> 00:20:52.450
You'll be able to meet any challenge.

00:20:52.450 --> 00:20:57.450
Jehovah is my light and my salvation.

00:20:57.450 --> 00:21:01.450
Jehovah helped the apostles, and he's going to help us.

00:21:01.450 --> 00:21:06.450
No matter the response, you made Jehovah happy today.

00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:10.450
It's harder to be courageous for yourself.

00:21:11.450 --> 00:21:14.450
We empathize with you, Brother Matthews.

00:21:14.450 --> 00:21:18.450
Can you tell us what you're doing right now to build courage?

00:21:18.450 --> 00:21:20.450
Absolutely.

00:21:20.450 --> 00:21:22.450
Here's my prescription.

00:21:22.450 --> 00:21:25.450
Regular prayer and study.

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:29.450
Application of the Bible's guidance.

00:21:29.450 --> 00:21:31.450
Attending as many meetings as I can.

00:21:31.450 --> 00:21:36.450
And, of course, preaching to others about our hope.

00:21:36.450 --> 00:21:39.450
That's a very good prescription.

00:21:39.450 --> 00:21:43.450
There's a particular scripture that has meaning for you right now.

00:21:43.450 --> 00:21:47.450
Right now, it's Hebrews chapter 11, verse 6.

00:21:47.450 --> 00:21:55.450
It says, moreover, without faith, it is impossible to please God well

00:21:55.450 --> 00:22:00.450
for whoever approaches God must believe that He is

00:22:00.450 --> 00:22:07.450
and that He becomes the rewarder of those earnestly seeking Him.

00:22:07.450 --> 00:22:12.450
So, even if I lose my eyesight, Brother Nicoletti,

00:22:12.450 --> 00:22:20.450
I will continue to seek Jehovah with my family and my eyes of faith.

00:22:20.450 --> 00:22:25.450
Thank you, Brother Matthews, for being such a good example of courage.
